(3, 'simultaneous', 'simultaneous', '同时的,同时存在的 (adj.)', 'adj.', '/,sɪm(ə)l''teɪnɪəs/', '{"meaning":"同时的,同时存在的 (adj.)","examples":["They grabbed each other’s hands in simultaneous panic. — 他们俩同时惊慌起来，相互抓住对方的手。","Up to twenty users can have simultaneous access to the system. — 最多可有20名用户同时登该系统。","The speeches will be broadcast live, with simultaneous translation (= immediate translation, as the person is speaking ) into English. — 这些演讲将作现场直播，并配有英语同声传译。"],"etymology":null}', 965),
(3, 'approximate', 'approximate', '近似的 (adj.)；(to)接近 (v.)；sim (adj.)', 'adj.', '/ə''prɒksɪmət/', '{"meaning":"近似的 (adj.)；(to)接近 (v.)；sim (adj.)","examples":["For each approximate solution of a parameterized problem, the app also displays the margin of error. — 对于每一个参数化问题的近似结果，这个程序也会显示误差的边界。","approximate solution — [计]近似解","approximate calculation — 近似计算"],"etymology":null}', 966),
(3, 'assimilate', 'assimilate', '吸收，消化；使同化 (v.)；被吸收；被同化 (v.)', 'v.', '/ə''sɪmɪleɪt/', '{"meaning":"吸收，消化；使同化 (v.)；被吸收；被同化 (v.)","examples":["It will take time to assimilate all these facts. — 充分掌握所有这些情况需要时间。"],"etymology":null}', 967),
(3, 'resume', 'resume', '个人简历 (n.)；再继续,重新开始;再用;恢复 (v.)', 'n.', '/rɪˈzjuːm; ˈrɛzjʊmeɪ/', '{"meaning":"个人简历 (n.)；再继续,重新开始;再用;恢复 (v.)","examples":["Don''t push for an interview on the spot, but rather explain that you want to let them know of your interest, drop off your resume, and complete an application while you''re there if possible. — 这个时候不要急着想得到面试，而是解释为你只是想让他们知道你对他们招聘的职位有兴趣，放下你的简历，然后有可能的话填完一份申请表就离开吧。","personal resume — 个人简历"],"etymology":null}', 968),
(3, 'assume', 'assume', '假装；假定，设想；承担；呈现，采取 (v.)', 'v.', '/ə''sjuːm/', '{"meaning":"假装；假定，设想；承担；呈现，采取 (v.)","examples":["I think we can safely assume (=  it is almost certain  ) that interest rates will go up again soon. — 我想我们几乎可以肯定，利率很快会再次上调。","When it got to midnight and Paul was still not back, I began to assume the worst (=  think that the worst possible thing had happened  ) . — 到午夜时保罗还没回来，我就开始往最坏的地方想了。","assume responsibility — 承担责任"],"etymology":null}', 969),
(3, 'assumption', 'assumption', '假定，设想；采取；承担；推测；假装 (n.)', 'n.', '/ə''sʌm(p)ʃ(ə)n/', '{"meaning":"假定，设想；采取；承担；推测；假装 (n.)","examples":["You would be making an assumption that''s not based on any fact that you could report. — 你会做出不以你能报道的任何事实为依据的一种假设。","on the assumption that — 假设","fundamental assumption — n. 基本假定"],"etymology":null}', 970),
(3, 'consume', 'consume', '消耗；吃完，喝光；(with)使着迷；烧毁 (v.)', 'v.', '/kən''sjuːm/', '{"meaning":"消耗；吃完，喝光；(with)使着迷；烧毁 (v.)","examples":["Only 27% of the paper we consume is recycled. — 我们消耗的纸张只有 27% 得到回收利用。","A smaller vehicle will consume less fuel. — 汽车小耗费燃料也少。","propensity to consume — 消费倾向"],"etymology":null}', 971),
(3, 'consumption', 'consumption', '消费(量),消耗 (n.)', 'n.', '/kən''sʌm(p)ʃ(ə)n/', '{"meaning":"消费(量),消耗 (n.)","examples":["Vigorous exercise increases oxygen consumption. — 剧烈运动增加氧的消耗。","energy consumption — [化]能量损耗","power consumption — 能量功耗"],"etymology":null}', 972),
(3, 'presume', 'presume', '假定,假设,认为,揣测,滥用,擅自行动 (v.)', 'v.', '/prɪ''zjuːm/', '{"meaning":"假定,假设,认为,揣测,滥用,擅自行动 (v.)","examples":["I presume you''re here on business. — 我想你是来这儿出差的吧。","\\"Had he been home all week?\\"—\\"I presume so.\\" — “他整个星期都在家吗？”—“我想是。”"],"etymology":null}', 973),
(3, 'sympathetic', 'sympathetic', '有同情心的；赞同的；n.交感神经 (adj.)', 'adj.', '/sɪmpə''θetɪk/', '{"meaning":"有同情心的；赞同的；n.交感神经 (adj.)","examples":["a sympathetic friend — 一个有同情心的朋友","a sympathetic attitude — 一种同情的态度","We hope always to provide a friendly sympathetic ear (= someone willing to listen to someone else’s problems ) . — 我们希望总能做到友善地倾听。"],"etymology":null}', 974),
(3, 'sympathize', 'sympathize', '(sympathise)(with)同情;共鸣,同感;赞成 (v.)', 'v.', '/''simpəθaiz/', '{"meaning":"(sympathise)(with)同情;共鸣,同感;赞成 (v.)","examples":["I sympathize, but I don’t know how to help. — 我很同情，但不知道如何帮忙。","sympathize with — 同情…；与…产生共鸣"],"etymology":null}', 975),
(3, 'sympathy', 'sympathy', '同情，同情心；赞同，同感；慰问 (n.)', 'n.', '/''sɪmpəθɪ/', '{"meaning":"同情，同情心；赞同，同感；慰问 (n.)","examples":["Our sympathies are with the families of the victims. — 我们向受害者家庭表示慰问。","sympathy for — 对…表示同情","sympathy with — 赞同；对…同情"],"etymology":null}', 976),
(3, 'symphony', 'symphony', '交响乐,交响曲 (n.)', 'n.', '/''sɪmf(ə)nɪ/', '{"meaning":"交响乐,交响曲 (n.)","examples":["Bruckner’s Fifth Symphony — 布鲁克纳的《第五交响曲》","symphony orchestra — 交响乐团","boston symphony orchestra — 波士顿交响乐团"],"etymology":null}', 977),
(3, 'symptom', 'symptom', '(疾病的)症状；(不好事情的)征兆,表征 (n.)', 'n.', '/''sɪm(p)təm/', '{"meaning":"(疾病的)症状；(不好事情的)征兆,表征 (n.)","examples":["One of the most common symptoms of schizophrenia is hearing imaginary voices. — 精神分裂症最常见的症状之一是幻听。","symptom complex — 症候群"],"etymology":null}', 978),
(3, 'sanction', 'sanction', '批准,同意,支持,认可 (n&v.)；处罚,制裁 (n.)', 'n&v.', '/''sæŋ(k)ʃ(ə)n/', '{"meaning":"批准,同意,支持,认可 (n&v.)；处罚,制裁 (n.)","examples":["Apparently, the aide had acted without White House sanction. — 这名助理的所作所为显然未经过白宫的批准。","legal sanction — n. 法律制裁","economic sanction — [经]经济制裁"],"etymology":null}', 979),
(3, 'sane', 'sane', '心智健全的,神志清醒的,明智的,稳健的 (adj.)', 'adj.', '/seɪn/', '{"meaning":"心智健全的,神志清醒的,明智的,稳健的 (adj.)","examples":["He seems perfectly sane (= completely sane ) to me. — 在我看来他神志完全正常。","No sane person would want to kill a baby. — 神志正常的人不会去杀一个婴儿。"],"etymology":null}', 980),
