(3, 'grave', 'grave', '重大的；严肃的；黯淡的 (adj.)；墓穴，坟墓；死亡 (n.)；雕刻；铭记 (v.)', 'adj.', '/greɪv/', '{"meaning":"重大的；严肃的；黯淡的 (adj.)；墓穴，坟墓；死亡 (n.)；雕刻；铭记 (v.)","examples":["Matthew’s life is in grave danger . — 马修的生命危在旦夕。","The report expressed grave concern over the technicians’ lack of training. — 报告中对技术人员缺乏培训深表忧虑。","I have grave doubts about his ability. — 我十分怀疑他的能力。"],"etymology":null}', 2506),
