(3, 'scare', 'scare', '惊吓；把…吓跑 (v.)；恐慌；惊吓；惊恐 (n.)；（美）骇人的 (adj.)', 'v.', '/skeə/', '{"meaning":"惊吓；把…吓跑 (v.)；恐慌；惊吓；惊恐 (n.)；（美）骇人的 (adj.)","examples":["I don’t scare easily, you know. — 你知道我不是那么容易给吓倒的！","scare away — 把…吓跑","scare buying — n. 抢购"],"etymology":null}', 3973),
(3, 'engagement', 'engagement', '婚约；约会；交战；诺言 (n.)', 'n.', '/ɪn''geɪdʒm(ə)nt; en-/', '{"meaning":"婚约；约会；交战；诺言 (n.)","examples":["Their engagement was announced in the paper. — 他们订婚的消息在报上公布了。","Tony was stunned when Lisa suddenly broke off their engagement (= finished it ). — 托尼对莉萨突然解除他俩的婚约感到震惊。"],"etymology":null}', 3974),
