(3, 'dirty', 'dirty', '下流的，卑鄙的；肮脏的；恶劣的；暗淡的 (adj.)；弄脏 (v.)', 'adj.', '/''dɜːtɪ/', '{"meaning":"下流的，卑鄙的；肮脏的；恶劣的；暗淡的 (adj.)；弄脏 (v.)","examples":["a stack of dirty dishes in the sink — 洗涤槽里的一堆脏碟子","How did you get so dirty? — 你怎么会弄得这么脏？","He was afraid the dog''s hairs might dirty the seats. — 他担心狗毛会把座椅弄脏。"],"etymology":null}', 3979),
(3, 'forecast', 'forecast', '预报，预测；预示 (v.)；预测，预报；预想 (n.)', 'v.', '/''fɔːkɑːst/', '{"meaning":"预报，预测；预示 (v.)；预测，预报；预想 (n.)","examples":["Rain was forecast for the weekend. — 预报周末有雨。","weather forecast — 天气预测，天气预报","demand forecast — 需求预测"],"etymology":null}', 3980),
(3, 'infrared', 'infrared', '红外线 (n.)；红外线的 (adj.)', 'n.', '/ɪnfrə''red/', '{"meaning":"红外线 (n.)；红外线的 (adj.)","examples":["Both the model and the satellite sensor use infrared energy to measure clouds. — 模型和卫星传感器都使用红外能量来进行云的估算。","\\"This is an exciting result, \\" says Tinetti. \\"This is the first near-infrared spectrum of a planet. — 迪奈蒂说：“这是个令人兴奋的结果，这是行星上发现的第一个近红外光谱。","His discovery of the electromagnetic spectrum led to the development of television, radio, microwaves, as well as aiding in the development of radio and infrared telescopes. — 他发现的电磁特性最终导致电视、广播、微波炉的发明，并且也对无线电和红外望远镜的发明起到了重要作用。"],"etymology":null}', 3981),
(3, 'mourn', 'mourn', '哀悼；忧伤；服丧 (v.)', 'v.', '/mɔːn/', '{"meaning":"哀悼；忧伤；服丧 (v.)","examples":["Hundreds of people gathered to mourn the slain president. — 成百上千人聚集在一起悼念遇刺的总统。","mourn for — 悼念；追悼","mourn over — 哀悼"],"etymology":null}', 3982),
(3, 'chill', 'chill', '寒冷；寒意；寒心 (n.)；寒冷的；冷漠的；扫兴的 (adj.)；冷冻，冷藏；使寒心；使感到冷 (v.)', 'n.', '/tʃɪl/', '{"meaning":"寒冷；寒意；寒心 (n.)；寒冷的；冷漠的；扫兴的 (adj.)；冷冻，冷藏；使寒心；使感到冷 (v.)","examples":["There was a slight chill in the air . — 空气中有些微的寒意。","I turned on the heater in the hall to take the chill off the house (= to heat it slightly ) . — 我开了厅里的暖气给屋子驱寒。","chill out — 冷静，冷静下来"],"etymology":null}', 3983),
(3, 'myth', 'myth', '神话；虚构的人，虚构的事 (n.)', 'n.', '/mɪθ/', '{"meaning":"神话；虚构的人，虚构的事 (n.)","examples":["a book of Greek myths — 一本关于希腊神话的图书","the giants of myth and fairytale — 神话和童话里的巨人"],"etymology":null}', 3984),
(3, 'clarity', 'clarity', '清楚，明晰；透明 (n.)', 'n.', '/''klærɪtɪ/', '{"meaning":"清楚，明晰；透明 (n.)","examples":["Letters may be edited for length and clarity. — 信件可能要加以修改以求篇幅合适，意思明了。","a lack of clarity in the law on property rights — 产权法律含糊不清"],"etymology":null}', 3985),
(3, 'whisky', 'whisky', '威士忌酒 (n.)；威士忌酒的 (adj.)', 'n.', '/''wɪskɪ/', '{"meaning":"威士忌酒 (n.)；威士忌酒的 (adj.)","examples":["We drink whisky mixed with beer. — 我们喝掺有啤酒的威士忌。","He drank another glass of whisky, but that didn''t support him to hit his wife. — 他又喝了一杯威士忌，可这仍然没能令他鼓起勇气去打他的妻子。","After drinking a small cup of whisky,he began to stroke the things happened in these two days. — 喝了一小杯威士忌酒之后，他开始理了理这一两天发生的事情。"],"etymology":null}', 3986),
(3, 'pretend', 'pretend', '假装，伪装，佯装 (v.)；假装的 (adj.)', 'v.', '/prɪ''tend/', '{"meaning":"假装，伪装，佯装 (v.)；假装的 (adj.)","examples":["Let’s pretend we’re on the moon. — 我们假装自己是在月球上吧。","He’s not asleep – he’s just pretending. — 他并没睡着，不过是装睡而已。","To pretend ignorance of the situation would be irresponsible. — 装作不知情是不负责任的做法。"],"etymology":null}', 3987),
(3, 'scan', 'scan', '扫描；浏览；细看；详细调查；标出格律 (v.)；扫描；浏览；审视；细看 (n.)', 'v.', '/skæn/', '{"meaning":"扫描；浏览；细看；详细调查；标出格律 (v.)；扫描；浏览；审视；细看 (n.)","examples":["He scanned the horizon, but there was no sign of the ship. — 他朝地平线处仔细眺望，但是找不到那艘船的踪影。","She scanned his face, looking for signs of what he was thinking. — 她端详着他的脸，想知道他在想些什么。","Video cameras scanned the car park. — 摄像机监视着停车场。"],"etymology":null}', 3988),
