(3, 'magnet', 'magnet', '磁铁；[电磁] 磁体；磁石 (n.)', 'n.', '/ˈmæɡnɪt/', '{"meaning":"磁铁；[电磁] 磁体；磁石 (n.)","examples":["It''s possible to hang a nail from a magnet and then use that nail to pick up another nail. — 把一颗钉子挂在一个磁体上再用这颗钉子去吸起另一颗钉子是可能的。","permanent magnet — 永久磁铁","superconducting magnet — 超导磁体；超导磁铁"],"etymology":null}', 3990),
